review_title: Excellent sound quality, joints feels somewhat fragile.
reviews:
I like these headphones.

Pros:
- Great noise cancellation.
- Excellent sound quality.
- Good price.
- Extra 24 month warranty if you register your purchase.

Cons:
- Feel slightly flimsy around the joints.
- A bit tight (but I have a big head, so you'll be fine).

It seems to reduce popping, but it also muffles overall volume. To compensate, I have to turn up my mic's gain, which adds more noise. So for my setup (narration at a distance of about 50cm), it's not worth having.

review_title: Such a taught, flat background. Crease-shadows are no more!
reviews:
I used to use a plain material green-screen backdrop. But no matter how I set things up, there would always be visible creases once the studio light were turned on.
This guy fixed that issue by pulling things taught. Would recommend.

I had to enlarge some of the ports in the case by filing away the plastic! The Pi wouldn't fit because the holes were too small. Seriously?
Once I fixed the case it was smooth sailing, but you can't expect your average buyer to have wood-working micro-files (the size of a headphone jack). Other issues include:
- The fan is pretty loud.
- The SD didn't come with all the OSes advertised.

review_title: Good enough. But plastic is warping after extensive use.
reviews: It does a good enough job, but after 6ish months of use the plastic has started to warp.

review_title: The replacement disk was ALSO damaged.
reviews: The first disk to arrive had such bad scratches on the disk that the console wouldn't recognise it. The replacement disk was also damaged (in the exact same pattern), just slightly less severe (i.e. it runs). I'm not actually reviewing game-play here, as it was a gift.

review_title: Tastes like the shells got ground up and left behind.
reviews:
I usually love walnuts, but not these. I'd understand the occasional piece of shell - but these leave a bitter taste as if every piece has shell-powder coating it.... I'm literally going to try washing these before I eat any more, that's how inedible these are.

EDIT: washing these a couple of times slightly reduced the bitterness (in case anyone else has something similar happen).

It did it's job, and seemed sturdy, but one day (without any extra jostling, tugging, or touching of any kind) it simply stopped working. Fortunately I bought 2, and the backup worked despite being coiled up tightly in a storage cupboard for 6 months.

review_title: Excellent for a large WUSH bag
reviews: 4 compartments give plenty of space for an emergency bag - I've managed to fit a small med kit, back up phone, backup batteries and plenty more. May get another for everyday use.
Good picture quality all the way down to the highest magnification. The only downside is the slightly unstable stand, but in my opinion it doesn't detract.

I'm using this is a local media server, but there are enough supported programs to do WAY more.
Pros:
- It's really easy to use once setup - initial setup is also easy, though not trivial.
- Lots of supported server-side apps means you can lots more than just run media.
- It's whisper quiet.
- Dim-able LEDs.
- With a WiFi dongle (not included) it can be setup anywhere, so you aren't tied to your router.

Cons:
- Supported audio/video formats are limited - and the server isn't powerful enough to convert them on the fly.
- Direct remote access is tricky (at least on Windows, Linux seems to connect easily).

review_title: It burns! But in a good way.
reviews:
It's a lot stronger than I expected, but it leaves me feeling clean. Good initial flavor and aftertaste.

I like a bit of burn, but if you have low sting tolerance, you might want to look for something less chili-like.
This is the only toothpaste I've found that actually helps with my sensitive molars. Flavor is fine, and it doesn't have a strong burn.

review_title: Easy to unbalance, but also easily adjusted
reviews:
It was easy to put together, and having a non-clamp mounting option made it far easier to attach it to my desk.

Just make sure you have enough monitors (of the right sizes) to spread the weight equally across the central axis. It's possible that a larger base could spread the weight out enough to prevent unwanted tilting - regardless I'd still buy it again.
Cat loves it, and the bag is huge, so I'll definitely be buying more - even it's 6 months before I need more :P

review_title: My cat seems to love it.
reviews: If I could afford to buy it more often I definitely would - my cat loves it.
The texturing on the thread probably impacts it's integrity. Good for accent work.
This is by far the cheapest Coke I've found listed anywhere - and the taste is exactly the same as normal. I'll be adding this to my list of subscription items ASAP.

review_title: These puts my existing blinds to shame
reviews: You could easily mistake midday for dawn with these guys installed. They've drastically helped with my light sensitive sleeping. Would buy again.
Our cat loves these, and brings them to use in the middle of night as gifts (loudly O_o).
The cat loved it. If I could afford to keep buying it I would.

review_title: You get what you pay for.
reviews: Too small and flimsy. Plus the promo image is misleading as it suggests matches are included.

My cat loves his catnip, but when exposed to the silver-vine he showed no more interest than if it had been a stick off the ground (which for all I know it could be). However, it may just be my cat's personal taste.

review_title: Quality seems ok, variety not so much
reviews: They came with 10 identical bits of one type, and 6 of another... I was expecting a wider variety of sizes. But they did the job I needed them for, so I can't complain too much.

By the end of the book, it felt like almost every faction involved (yes, even Thinking Machines) had unanswered questions. It's been a long time since I read Houses of Dune - but so far as I can tell the answered questions look like they are simply lost to the +-10,000 years dividing those 2 trilogies.
Good material, warmer than expected, and nice customer support. Would buy another in a different color.

review_title: A gelatinous lump that my cat won't touch
reviews:
This isn't like any of the other Weruva variants I've tried - it is a single gelatinous lump, more like what you'd see with a discount brand. My cat isn't fussy - at all - but the most he'll do is lick off some of the gravy... even after 3 days of being given no alternative he still won't eat it, so now I have to find an alternative (I refuse to let my kitty go on a hunger strike).

Don't risk it, and don't waste your money.

I have mixed feelings about this litter.
Pros:
- Clumps really well
- Flushable
Cons:
- So light that it sticks to my cat's paws (getting strewn throughout the house).
- 1 bag/box only fills 1.5 litter-trays... which for the price is not good.

I'd probably keep using it if it was cheaper.
Will definitely be buying more in the future.

review_title: Beautiful and great value for money.
reviews: My wife loved these, they were far larger than expected.

The promo pictures are definitely Photoshopped - my cat can barely even fit in the opening, let alone lie down. It's a fold-out material-only body... making it really easy for a boisterous cat to tip over.
Cat isn't too interested in it (yet), but it's still a nice toy.

review_title: Tough yet comfortable - I especially appreciate how easily the pants tighten/release ...
reviews:
Tough yet comfortable - I especially appreciate how easily the pants tighten/release compared to my old Gis. The only downside was a slight fading after 2 or 3 washes - but that's only really noticeable when you compare brand-new and slightly-used (I bought 2).
It was slightly larger than expected, but one run through the tumble-dryer shrank it to the prefect size ^_^

review_title: and they are easy to fit behind other furniture (making them unobtrusive)
reviews: I've already bought 2, and will probably buy 2 more for the bedroom. Their shades turn a harsh bulb into a gentle glow, and they are easy to fit behind other furniture (making them unobtrusive)
Good bike for the price. My only real complaint is that when changing gear, they'll often slip and change several levels at once (which can be quite jarring).

review_title: It doesn't last as long as I'd like, but both the look and smell more than ...
reviews: It doesn't last as long as I'd like, but both the look and smell more than make up for that. Would buy again.

review_title: Less than a week of use and the clasp broke ...
reviews: Less than a week of use and the clasp broke. I didn't drop it, or overfill it. I'm keeping my brand new wallet closed with an elastic band O_o

review_title: The HDD vs SSD drive mounts are a little too ...
reviews: The HDD vs SSD drive mounts are a little too far apart, but with an extra length cable it stops being an issue. Otherwise a SOLID case.

review_title: The video quality is crisp and clear. I haven't ...
reviews: The video quality is crisp and clear. I haven't used it's mic, but that's because I have a stand-alone mic.

review_title: Useful... just be prepared for unpleasant surprises.
reviews: It's terrifying what this thing makes glow... just shine it on a pillow and you'll realise how much skin and hair is hiding there. It was especially traumatizing using this in the bathroom, more so because I just moved in so the 'mess' isn't mine *shudder*

review_title: Would buy again - maybe as a gift
reviews: This was so worth it's price. No bloatware, and rooted right out the gate, awesome. The Android flavour took a bit of getting used to (coming from a Samsung-only background) - but that's definitely not a deal breaker.

The humidity monitor updates quickly and accurately - the temperature guage is slow to change and often doesn't get cold enough (there's no way a room in Toronto, with windows open, in winter, is 24C). But it does get the higher temperature right, and that's what I care about.
Fits the bet well, easy to put on, doesn't detract from the comfort of the mattress.

review_title: ... of the most sturdy/expensive material - but they look good and do their job just fine
reviews: They aren't made of the most sturdy/expensive material - but they look good and do their job just fine. As a bonus, the screws they provide match the style which is nice.
Every other lunch is now a fruit&veggie smoothie. I'm really happy with it.

review_title: You get WAY more than you pay for.
reviews: Exceptionally comfortable considering the price, firmer than I personally like but still comfy. You easily pay 5 times as much for the same quality else-ware.

review_title: Better as a decorative side table than a work-desk.
reviews:
It looks nice... but it is unstable AF. Somehow the dimensions are off, so it never has all of its feet on the ground at one. Better as a decorative side table than a work-desk.
EDIT - 2 weeks of use and the paint beneath my mouse has started to wear away. A mouse pad isn't an option given the desk's size... so yeah really worthless.

review_title: but for the price they are definitely good
reviews: Nothing special, but for the price they are definitely good enough
Really good looking, would buy again if I had a second bathroom :P
Protected by 3 different plastic sleeves. Card was mint condition. Would buy again.
Good sound quality, easy to use.
Warm and comfy.
It's nothing special, but for the price it more than delivers as a work monitor.
They aren't as wooly/fluffy as I expected, but still good.
I weight 90kg, I'm using it for 8 hours a day, and hasn't shown any wear/leaks/distortion.
Simple to set up, sturdy, and my 6 year old mic somehow fits perfectly.
Brought my old camera back to life, and came fully charged
These fit like... well like a glove. The pinky fingers a tiny bit too long for me, but that doesn't get in the way. Very warm, very comfy, would buy again.
